  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Interior Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage design projects from concept to completion, including installation.</li>\n  <li>Develop design concepts, mood boards, and space plans that meet client needs and budgets.</li>\n  <li>Produce detailed technical drawings and documentation using CAD software.</li>\n  <li>Select and specify all furniture, fixtures, equipment (FF&amp;E), materials, and finishes.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with contractors, vendors, and architects to ensure design execution.</li>\n  <li>Conduct site visits to monitor progress, quality, and resolve issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Interior Design or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience as an Interior Designer with a strong portfolio.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in AutoCAD, SketchUp, and the Adobe Creative Suite.</li>\n  <li>Excellent knowledge of space planning, materials, furnishings, and building codes.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication, presentation, and project management skills.</li>\n</ul>",
